The paper deals with the problem of online matching on the line, which is a problem in the field of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses lower bounds for the problem, which is related to game theory (cs.GT) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper uses techniques such as symmetry and local information, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.SI).
